40extern int local_flag;

42int
43dump(struct dump_options *opt, int argc, char **argv)
44{
45 krb5_error_code ret;
46 FILE *f;
47 struct hdb_print_entry_arg parg;
48 HDB *db = NULL;
49
50 if (!local_flag) {
51 krb5_warnx(context, "dump is only available in local (-l) mode");
52 return 0;
53 }
54
55 db = _kadm5_s_get_db(kadm_handle);
56
57 if (argc == 0)
58 f = stdout;
59 else
60 f = fopen(argv[0], "w");
61
62 if (f == NULL) {
63 krb5_warn(context, errno, "open: %s", argv[0]);
64 goto out;
65 }
66 ret = db->hdb_open(context, db, O_RDONLY, 0600);
67 if (ret) {
68 krb5_warn(context, ret, "hdb_open");
69 goto out;
70 }
71
72 if (!opt->format_string || strcmp(opt->format_string, "Heimdal") == 0) {
73 parg.fmt = HDB_DUMP_HEIMDAL;
74 } else if (opt->format_string && strcmp(opt->format_string, "MIT") == 0) {
75 parg.fmt = HDB_DUMP_MIT;
76 fprintf(f, "kdb5_util load_dump version 5\n"); /* 5||6, either way */
77 } else {
78 krb5_errx(context, 1, "Supported dump formats: Heimdal and MIT");
79 }
80 parg.out = f;
81 hdb_foreach(context, db, opt->decrypt_flag ? HDB_F_DECRYPT : 0,
82 hdb_print_entry, &parg);
83
84 db->hdb_close(context, db);
85out:
86 if(f && f != stdout)
87 fclose(f);
88 return 0;
89}
